# The ASCII-Table widget is the simplest way to work with tables!

# Here’s a quick guide:

# 1. Press Ctrl + Enter (or Command + Enter on macOS) to execute the example below.
# 2. Press Ctrl + Z (or Command + Z on macOS) to undo your previous actions.
# 3. You can use either CIF or CFL notation.
# 4. To delete a column simply rename it to “dd” or “Delete”.
# 5. To plot a graph, append “(x)”, “(y)”, “(sy)”, “(y2)” to the column names for example “Column-1(x)”.
# 6. To multiply a column by 2, append “(*2)” to its name for example “Column-1(*2)”.
# 7. The popup window will try to predict your input; use Tab to accept suggestions.